<font color="#FF0000">DEMONS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct  2 18:26:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Enjoyed discovering the site, and partic. the letter about Glenn's retort to Metzenbaum. Don't we all wish we'd said that... Flew Dustoff out of Long Binh and Cu Chi (right over the tunnels and didn't know it!) from Feb '70 to Feb 71. This past July went to the VietVet. Helicopter Pilot's reunion down here in Orlando and that was eerie to be sure. Somehow they had dragged through a very tight doorway, with inches to spare, into the frickin' ballroom, mind you, two Hueys and a Cobra! I was standing by the dance floor away from the aircraft and bumped into a bearded guy who said this was his first reunion and then told me a little bit about his personal healing process, which had begun for him only recently. &quot;Yeah,&quot; he said, &quot;I'm doin' pretty well now, but for some reason, I just can't go near the Huey...&quot; Demons indeed.<br><br>
Re McNamara: the August 10, 1997 New York Times Magazine by David Shipler about him and his demons is a must-read. As is, speaking of more demons, if you can find it, the full story of a man who searches for and finally meets his victim. This man, now a minister, was part of the Air Force team responsible for that bombing mission, actually, that napalming mission which we all know went so well. We see the photograph and we KNOW it is successful because the little girl, naked, burned and screaming, comes running up the road to tell us.<br><br>

